@sleuth_zw Alright. I was stating what the point of looting in this situation is. Hear me out: Looting during natural disasters is bad. Theft is bad. However if the people want change they'd have to deal as much disruption to the system and society. We've seen this in Hong Kong.
.
Another thing is that I heard that the looting started because Target wouldn't sell milk to treat gas used by the police. And about why "peaceful protests wouldn't work", I'll leave you to ask a Hong Kong protestor, or a supporter of them. They know why and may even have experience with challenging the system.
